Program: Omnibus
Title: British Jews from Socialism to Thatcherism
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jt8
Last Broadcast Date: 16 March 1990
A look at the history of Anglo-Jewry and how and why the politics of the British Jewish community has developed and gradually moved from socialism to conservatism. Contributors include Jonathan Sacks and Sir Alfred Sherman.